     As recommended in previous studies


       2

      ,

       41


     , we conducted our analyses using SIA, with the exception of the RILE analysis, which uses SIE for consistency with prior RILE studies


       23

      ,

       25


     .

The second criterion used here was that the day of the minimum daily SIA from the simulations between 1980 and 2014 falls within the observational range of day 238 (August 26, from the CDR SIA data


  17


) to day 272 (Sept 29, from the NASA Team SIA data


  17


), plus/minus 5 days (the average standard deviation of the sea ice minimum day over 1980–2014 from the models with more than 5 members). As for the first criterion, if any ensemble member from a model fell within the observational range, the criterion was considered to be met. We chose this second criterion to ensure that models simulate the daily minimum at a time comparable to observations, since the focus of this study is on the first ice-free day.

